{"lemma":"سِيلان","slug":"سِيلان","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21463"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَالَ (sāla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flow, flux","examples":[{"text":"سَيَلَان الدَّم","english":"the flow of blood"},{"text":"سَيَلَان الدُّمُوع","english":"the flow of tears"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gonorrhea, tripper"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sa.ja.laːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21463","headword_ar":"سِيلَانٌ","root":"syl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sinox","text_ar":"سِنْخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that enters into"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hilt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"handle, of a sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a knife"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) in the A the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that enters into the hilt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"handle, of a sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a knife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"heard by A'Obeyd, though not from a learned man: (S, TA:) but AA cites the following ex. from Ez-Zibrikán Ibn-Bedr:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walano A^uSaAliHakumo maA daAmo liY farasN\n                      \n                     \n                        waA@$otad~a qaboDFA EalaY Als~iylaAni A_ibohaAmiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I will not make peace with you while I have a horse and my thumb grasps firmly upon the tongue of the sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (El-Jawáleekee, IB, TA.) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayaAlN","text_ar":"سَيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayaAlapN","text_ar":"سَيَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [or rather the former is a coll. gen. n. of which the latter is the n. un., applied in the present day to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of mimosa,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acacia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by Forskal in his Flora Aegypt. Arab., pp. lvi. and cxxiv., and by Delile in his Floræ Aegypt. Illustr. (in the Descr. de l'Égypte), no. 965: and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of thistle; carduus lacteus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild artichoke:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of trees having thorns, of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain trees having white thorns:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorny plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abah","text_ar":"شَبَه"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to have white thorns, from which, when these are plucked, there issues what resembles milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, M, K: *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain trees having lank branches and white thorns of which the bases resemble the middle pairs of the teeth of virgins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, (K,) accord. to Aboo-Ziyád, (AHn, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samur","text_ar":"سَمُر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gum-acacia-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AHn, M, K:) accord. to the A, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAf","text_ar":"خِلَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[now applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salix Aegyptia"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.] in the dial. of El-Yemen. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","TA","AA","AHn"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86/","headword_ar":"سيلان","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_15","lexicon_en":"Ibn Mālik, al-Alfāẓ al-Mukhtalifa fī l-Maʿānī al-Muʾtalifa (d. 1274 CE)","lexicon_ar":"الألفاظ المختلفة في المعاني المؤتلفة لابن مالك","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22418#8b889e","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">بَاب السيلان</span><br><br><span>وكفت وهمعت وذرفت وسكبت وسحت وهطلت وَدرت وسربت وارفضت وهملت وانهملت وهراقت وأراقت وفاضت وغربت وهتنت ودفقت وصابت ونبعث ونبعقت</span>"}]}}